According to a report by Intel Market Research, the India Strontium Carbonate Market was valued at USD 45 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 47 million in 2025 to USD 59 million by 2032, registering a CAGR of 4.6% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing stable expansion, supported by increasing demand from India's flourishing ceramics, electronics, glass manufacturing, and pyrotechnics industries. Strontium carbonate, an inorganic compound widely used in ferrite magnets, ceramic glazes, specialty glass, and fireworks, continues to play an essential role across multiple industrial sectors. As India strengthens its domestic manufacturing ecosystem through initiatives such as Make in India and Production Linked Incentive (PLI) schemes, demand for high-quality industrial and electronic-grade strontium carbonate is expected to rise steadily over the coming years.
